post_text:
September 12, 2020

Dear School Community Member,

We have been advised by the Department of Public Health that an employee has tested positive for COVID-19. At this time, based on available information there were no exposures to our school district, as the employee was not on campus within the last 14 days.

Remote learning will commence on September 14, 2020, as planned for. All building related functions will continue as normal. As always, the health and safety of our students and staff remains our top priority.

Sincerely yours,

Ivan J. Katz, Ed.D.

Superintendent of Schools

Dear School Community Member:
Gov. Andrew Cuomo announced on March 27th that schools would remain closed until April 15th because of the coronavirus pandemic, at which time the situation would be reassessed.
The Fallsburg Central School District will continue serving meals daily, Monday through Friday, for as long as schools are closed. Additionally, we are continuing our plans to begin our instructional rollout on April 3rd.
Updates will continue as new information comes in.
Thank you!

Dr. Katz

post_text:
Dear Parents and Guardians:

Meal deliveries began this morning and will take place daily from 9:00 AM - 11:00 AM. We are delivering food, by bus, to each regular bus stop. We are also making meals available for pick-up at the entrance of BCES for any family who wants to access meals that way. If you have any questions about meal delivery or pick-up, please email us at:

meals@fallsburgcsd.net

I appreciate the phone calls and emails to the district that indicate your preference to not have meals delivered to your homes. It will take us a couple of days to straighten all of those requests out but we will get it done!

Our primary objective is to get our children fed and we are making that happen! I am very proud of the grand team effort and support to make this a reality! I would also like to thank district staff and community members who have offered to volunteer. At this time we have the support that we need. However, if we need additional support, we will reach out to you.

Thank you one and all! Please stay healthy!

Ivan J. Katz, Ed.D
Superintendent of Schools

post_text:
Fallsburg Central School District Receives Platinum Award for Excellence
At The Worksite Wellness Summit held at New Hope Community Auditorium on October 4, 2019, Fallsburg Central School District received a "Platinum Award for Excellence in recognition of their commitment to health and wellness in Sullivan County." In the photo left to right are members of the FCSD Wellness Committee, Cornell Cooperative Extension's Sue Ann Boyd, FCSD Food Services Director Dara Smith, FCSD Wellness Committee Chair Suzanne Lendzian, first grade teacher Leah Exner, and FCSD Superintendent Dr. Ivan Katz

BCES Honors Superhero Students
The October Superheroes at Benjamin Cosor Elementary School received their honors in the School Cafeteria on the 30th of the month with a special pancake breakfast. The special breakfast was awarding students from all grade levels certificates of outstanding behavior during the second month of school. The group earned â€œSuperheroesâ€ Identity Cards with their photos and expandable bracelets that say â€œStand Up, Speak Out Against Bullying.â€ The theme for the month was Anti-Bullying.
Special thanks go out to the PBIS Team Coordinators, Nicole Cortes and Brittany Davis, and the cafeteria staff for decorating, preparing and serving the delicious food.

The Fallsburg Central School District will be on lockout at this time. While there is no threat against the school, I have been contacted by law enforcement to let me know that they are dealing with some threats made in the County. We are going on lockout out of an abundance of caution.
